    INSERT INTO lessons (module_id, title, description, content, order_index, duration_minutes, brief_content, action_items, resources) VALUES
    (v_module_id, 'Press Release Writing Fundamentals', 'Master the structure and style of effective press releases.',
    'Complete guide to press release writing.', 1, 45,
    'Press releases remain a primary tool for communicating news to media, despite evolving media consumption patterns. A well-crafted press release gets picked up; a poorly written one gets deleted.

The inverted pyramid structure places the most important information first: Lead paragraph answers who, what, when, where, why, and how. Supporting paragraphs provide context and details. Background information and boilerplate close the release.

Essential press release components: Headline (attention-grabbing, factual), Subhead (adds context), Dateline (city and date), Lead paragraph (core news), Body paragraphs (details, quotes, context), Boilerplate (company description), and Contact information.

Headlines must be specific and newsworthy. Compare: Bad: "Startup Launches New Product" versus Good: "Bengaluru Fintech Startup Raises ₹50 Cr to Expand UPI Payment Solutions to Tier-2 Cities." Include numbers, names, and specific outcomes when possible.

Lead paragraphs should stand alone. If a journalist reads only the first paragraph, they should understand the complete news. Avoid throat-clearing or background—get to the news immediately.

Quotes humanize releases. Include quotes from founders, executives, investors, or partners. Good quotes add perspective, not just restate facts. Avoid corporate jargon in quotes—make them sound like real human speech.

Indian press release considerations: Include INR amounts with conversions where relevant, Provide context on market size and opportunity, Reference government policies or regulations if applicable, and Include regional language translations for local media.

Length should be 400-600 words for most announcements. Complex stories (funding rounds, major partnerships) may extend to 800 words. Never exceed one page for standard news.

Formatting matters: Use professional letterhead, Include clear FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE or EMBARGOED headers, Provide clear contact details, and Use proper spacing and readable fonts.',
    '[{"task": "Create a press release template following standard structure", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Write practice releases for 3 hypothetical announcements", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Review 10 successful startup press releases to identify patterns", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Develop a quote library for various announcement types", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "PR Newswire Style Guide", "url": "https://www.prnewswire.com/resources/", "type": "guide"}, {"title": "BusinessWire India", "url": "https://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/home/", "type": "service"}, {"title": "PRWeb Distribution", "url": "https://www.prweb.com/", "type": "service"}, {"title": "Hemingway Editor for Clarity", "url": "https://hemingwayapp.com/", "type": "tool"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'Distribution Strategies', 'Maximize press release reach through strategic distribution.',
    'Getting your news to the right audiences.', 2, 40,
    'Writing a great press release means nothing without effective distribution. Strategic distribution ensures your news reaches journalists likely to cover it and audiences who care about it.

Distribution channels in India: Wire services (PR Newswire, BusinessWire, India PRWire) provide broad distribution but cost ₹15,000-₹50,000 per release. They reach news desks but do not guarantee coverage. Direct outreach to targeted journalists often yields better results for startups.

Direct distribution best practices: Build a targeted media list by beat and outlet, Personalize the email subject line and introduction, Send during optimal times (Tuesday-Thursday, 9-11 AM IST), Follow up once after 48 hours if no response, and Track opens and responses to optimize future outreach.

Email subject lines matter enormously. Include the news hook, not just "Press Release." Example: "[For Inc42] Bengaluru Startup X Raises ₹25 Cr Series A" is far more effective than "Press Release from Company X."

Embargo strategies: Embargoes give journalists time to prepare stories for simultaneous publication. Offer 24-48 hour embargoes for major news. Only embargo truly significant announcements—journalists dislike unnecessary embargoes. Honor embargoes absolutely—breaking embargo destroys journalist trust permanently.

Exclusive offers: Offering exclusives to top-tier publications increases coverage likelihood for major news. Tier your exclusives strategically—Economic Times exclusive, then second-tier publications, then wide distribution.

Timing considerations for India: Avoid major festivals and holidays, Consider IPL and cricket match days, Avoid Budget week for non-policy news, Monday mornings and Friday afternoons get less attention, and Align with industry events where relevant.

Track and measure distribution effectiveness: Open rates and click-through rates, Coverage generated per release, Share of voice changes, Journalist engagement patterns, and ROI per distribution channel.',
    '[{"task": "Build a tiered media distribution list with 100+ contacts", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Set up email tracking for press release distribution", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Create an editorial calendar aligning releases with news cycles", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Evaluate wire service options and costs for major announcements", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "PR Newswire India", "url": "https://www.prnewswire.co.in/", "type": "service"}, {"title": "BusinessWire India", "url": "https://www.businesswireindia.com/", "type": "service"}, {"title": "Mailtrack for Email Tracking", "url": "https://mailtrack.io/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "Cision Media Database", "url": "https://www.cision.com/", "type": "database"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'News Angles and Story Hooks', 'Identify newsworthy angles that capture journalist interest.',
    'Finding stories that journalists want to cover.', 3, 45,
    'Not every company update warrants a press release. Understanding what makes news helps you identify genuinely newsworthy moments and craft compelling angles for your announcements.

Newsworthy criteria journalists apply: Timeliness (is it happening now?), Significance (does it matter to many people?), Proximity (is it relevant to their audience?), Prominence (are notable people or companies involved?), Conflict (is there tension or debate?), Human interest (does it tell a compelling human story?), and Novelty (is it genuinely new or different?).

Common startup news hooks: Funding announcements (with investor context), Product launches (with market impact), Milestone achievements (users, revenue, growth), Strategic partnerships or acquisitions, Executive hires (for senior roles), Industry data and research findings, Company expansions (new markets, offices), and Award recognitions.

Strengthening weak news: Add data and numbers to provide scale, Connect to broader trends or policy changes, Include customer or market impact stories, Offer exclusive access or interviews, and Provide research or survey data.

Creating news when there is none obvious: Commission industry research and release findings, Comment on relevant breaking news or policy changes, Publish thought leadership with unique perspectives, and Celebrate company or customer milestones creatively.

Indian-specific angle opportunities: Policy and regulation changes affecting your sector, Government scheme participation and benefits, India market size and opportunity stories, Comparison with global markets and players, Regional expansion and Bharat opportunity, and Job creation and employment impact.

Test angles before committing: Share potential angles with friendly journalists for feedback, Monitor what similar companies generate coverage with, Track which angles your competitors use successfully, and A/B test subject lines to see what resonates.

Avoid false news hooks: Do not manufacture controversy, Do not exaggerate achievements, Do not bury bad news in good news releases, and Be truthful about funding amounts and metrics.',
    '[{"task": "Create an angle development framework for evaluating news potential", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Identify 10 potential news angles for your company over next 6 months", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Develop data or research that could generate news coverage", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Build relationships with journalists to test potential angles", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "News Values Theory", "url": "https://www.britannica.com/topic/news-media", "type": "education"}, {"title": "HARO (Help a Reporter Out)", "url": "https://www.helpareporter.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Qwoted Expert Sources", "url": "https://www.qwoted.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Google Trends for Angle Discovery", "url": "https://trends.google.com/", "type": "tool"}]');

