    INSERT INTO lessons (module_id, title, description, content, order_index, duration_minutes, brief_content, action_items, resources) VALUES
    (v_module_id, 'Community Strategy Fundamentals', 'Develop a strategic approach to community building.',
    'Building community with purpose and strategy.', 1, 45,
    'Brand communities create loyal advocates who amplify your message, provide feedback, and support each other. In India, where word-of-mouth drives significant purchase decisions, community building delivers outsized PR and brand value.

Community value for brands: Organic amplification of brand messages, Customer feedback and product insights, Peer-to-peer support reducing service costs, User-generated content creation, Brand advocacy and referrals, and Crisis buffer through goodwill.

Community types to consider: Customer communities (users helping users), Industry communities (professionals in your space), Geographic communities (regional user groups), Interest communities (around shared passions), and Partner communities (ecosystem participants).

Platform options for community: Owned platforms (custom forums, community apps), Social platforms (LinkedIn Groups, Facebook Groups), Communication platforms (Slack, Discord, WhatsApp), Physical community (meetups, events, chapters), and Hybrid approaches combining multiple platforms.

Community strategy elements: Purpose (why should members participate?), Target members (who do you want?), Value proposition (what do members get?), Engagement model (how will they participate?), Content strategy (what content fuels engagement?), Moderation approach (how will you maintain quality?), and Success metrics (how will you measure impact?).

Building community versus audience: Audience consumes your content passively, Community members interact with each other, Community requires ongoing investment and nurturing, and Community value compounds over time.

Community readiness assessment: Do you have enough users/followers to seed community? Do you have resources to manage and moderate? Is there natural interest in connection among your audience? Can you provide sufficient value to justify participation?

Start small and focused: Begin with core enthusiasts, not broad reach, Create value before scaling, Learn what works before major investment, and Quality engagement matters more than member count.',
    '[{"task": "Define community purpose and target member profile", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Evaluate platform options against your needs and resources", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Create community value proposition and engagement model", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Identify 20 potential founding members to seed community", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Circle Community Platform", "url": "https://circle.so/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Discord for Communities", "url": "https://discord.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Slack for Community", "url": "https://slack.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Community Building Guide by CMX", "url": "https://cmxhub.com/", "type": "resource"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'Community Engagement and Growth', 'Drive active engagement and sustainable growth.',
    'Growing engaged community members.', 2, 45,
    'Building a community is just the beginning—sustaining engagement and growing membership requires ongoing strategy and effort. Successful communities feel alive; inactive communities die.

Launching community successfully: Seed with engaged founding members, Establish norms and expectations early, Create initial content and discussions, Be highly present in early days, Celebrate early wins and contributions, and Iterate based on member feedback.

Driving ongoing engagement: Regular content and discussion prompts, Member spotlight features, Expert AMA (Ask Me Anything) sessions, Challenges and collaborative activities, Exclusive resources and content, and Recognition for active contributors.

Community content strategy: Educational content members value, Discussion prompts generating conversation, Member-generated content encouragement, Behind-the-scenes and exclusive access, and User success story celebrations.

Growing community membership: Referral programs rewarding member invitations, Integration with product onboarding, Promotion through owned channels, Partnership with complementary communities, Public showcase of community value, and Selective outreach to ideal members.

Community engagement metrics: Daily/weekly active members, Posts and comments per member, Member retention rates, Time spent in community, Net Promoter Score, and Referral activity.

Moderation and quality: Establish clear community guidelines, Train moderators on consistent enforcement, Balance open discussion with quality standards, Address conflicts promptly and fairly, and Remove bad actors quickly to protect culture.

Community team roles: Community manager (day-to-day engagement), Moderators (quality and guideline enforcement), Content creators (fuel for engagement), and Executive sponsor (strategic direction).',
    '[{"task": "Create community guidelines and moderation policies", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Develop a 4-week engagement content calendar", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Design a member recognition and spotlight program", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Build a community growth funnel from awareness to active membership", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Community Canvas Template", "url": "https://community-canvas.org/", "type": "template"}, {"title": "Orbit Community Analytics", "url": "https://orbit.love/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "Common Room Community Intelligence", "url": "https://www.commonroom.io/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "Community Led Growth Guide", "url": "https://www.commsor.com/", "type": "resource"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'Community Events and Programs', 'Create events and programs that strengthen community.',
    'Events and programs for community engagement.', 3, 40,
    'Events and structured programs create memorable community experiences, deepen relationships, and provide engagement peaks that sustain ongoing activity.

Virtual event types: Webinars and educational sessions, Member networking sessions, Product workshops and training, Expert panels and discussions, Virtual social gatherings, and Online conferences and summits.

Physical event opportunities: Meetups in key cities, Annual community conference, Pop-up events at industry conferences, Office visits and tours, Customer appreciation events, and Regional chapter gatherings.

Event planning essentials: Clear purpose and value proposition, Target attendance and format, Budget and resource requirements, Promotion and registration strategy, Content and speaker preparation, and Follow-up and engagement capture.

Indian event considerations: Consider time zones for virtual events (IST works broadly), Account for regional festival calendars, Hybrid formats reach broader audiences, Regional language options for broader inclusion, and Budget-conscious options for early-stage communities.

Structured program ideas: Mentorship matching programs, Certification or learning programs, Ambassador or champion programs, Beta testing and feedback programs, Content contribution programs, and Referral incentive programs.

Champion and ambassador programs: Identify most engaged members, Provide exclusive access and recognition, Equip with tools and resources, Set expectations for participation, Recognize and reward contribution, and Create community among champions.

Measuring event and program success: Attendance and participation rates, Post-event satisfaction scores, Community engagement lift after events, Referrals generated through programs, Business outcomes (leads, referrals, retention), and Content generated from events.',
    '[{"task": "Plan and execute your first community event", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Design a community champion or ambassador program", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Create an annual community events calendar", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Develop event playbooks for repeatable execution", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Luma Event Platform", "url": "https://lu.ma/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "Hopin Virtual Events", "url": "https://hopin.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Meetup.com", "url": "https://www.meetup.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Bevy Community Events", "url": "https://www.bevy.com/", "type": "platform"}]');

    -- MODULE 11: Regional Media Strategies
    INSERT INTO modules (product_id, title, description, order_index, duration_days)
    VALUES (v_product_id, 'Regional Media Strategies', 'Master PR across India diverse regional markets.', 11, 4)
    RETURNING id INTO v_module_id;

    INSERT INTO lessons (module_id, title, description, content, order_index, duration_minutes, brief_content, action_items, resources) VALUES
    (v_module_id, 'Regional Media Landscape', 'Understand India diverse regional media ecosystems.',
    'Navigating regional media across India.', 1, 45,
    'India is not one market—it is many markets with distinct languages, cultures, and media ecosystems. Regional media often has higher trust and engagement than national English publications. Effective PR requires regional strategy.

Regional media importance: Regional language publications reach massive audiences, Trust levels often exceed English media, Local business coverage is more accessible, Regional success stories resonate powerfully, and Political and cultural nuances require local understanding.

Major regional media markets: Hindi belt (UP, MP, Bihar, Rajasthan): Dainik Jagran, Amar Ujala, Hindustan, Navbharat Times. Maharashtra: Maharashtra Times, Loksatta, Lokmat. Tamil Nadu: Dinamalar, Dinakaran, Tamil Murasu. Karnataka: Vijaya Karnataka, Prajavani, Kannada Prabha. West Bengal: Ananda Bazar Patrika, Bartaman, Sangbad Pratidin. Andhra Pradesh/Telangana: Eenadu, Sakshi, Andhra Jyothy. Gujarat: Gujarat Samachar, Sandesh, Divya Bhaskar. Kerala: Malayala Manorama, Mathrubhumi, Madhyamam.

Regional media approach: Invest in local language communication, Work with regional PR agencies or freelancers, Adapt messaging for cultural context, Build relationships with regional journalists, and Create region-specific content and angles.

Regional business publications: Many regions have business-focused publications or supplements. Identify and build relationships with business desk editors and reporters covering entrepreneurship and business.

Regional television and digital: Regional news channels cover local business stories, Digital platforms have regional editions, and YouTube and social media have massive regional audiences.

Translation versus transcreation: Direct translation often fails—transcreation adapts meaning for cultural context. Work with native speakers, not just translators, and test messaging with regional audience samples.',
    '[{"task": "Map regional media landscape for your key geographic markets", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Build regional media lists with journalist contacts", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Identify regional PR agencies or freelancers to partner with", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Create transcreated messaging for top 3 regional languages", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Dainik Jagran", "url": "https://www.jagran.com/", "type": "publication"}, {"title": "Malayala Manorama", "url": "https://www.manoramaonline.com/", "type": "publication"}, {"title": "Eenadu", "url": "https://www.eenadu.net/", "type": "publication"}, {"title": "Gujarat Samachar", "url": "https://www.gujaratsamachar.com/", "type": "publication"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'Regional PR Execution', 'Execute effective PR campaigns in regional markets.',
    'Implementing regional PR strategies.', 2, 40,
    'Regional PR execution requires different approaches than national English media. Understanding local news cycles, cultural sensitivities, and journalist preferences enables effective regional coverage.

Regional press release adaptation: Translate and transcreate—do not just convert, Include region-specific context and relevance, Use local examples and reference points, Adapt quotes for cultural appropriateness, and Include local contact information.

Regional journalist engagement: Build relationships through local events, Engage in regional language on social media, Provide exclusives to regional publications, Respect local customs and communication styles, and Consider regional festival and holiday timing.

Regional story angles: Local job creation and economic impact, Regional customer success stories, State-specific policy and scheme alignment, Local partnerships and collaborations, Founder regional connection (if applicable), and Regional expansion announcements.

Regional event PR: Tie PR to regional events and festivals, Launch products with regional customization, Participate in regional industry conferences, Host regional media roundtables, and Create region-specific content moments.

Regional spokesperson preparation: Train spokespersons for regional media interviews, Prepare for regional language interviews if possible, Brief on regional cultural considerations, and Provide region-specific talking points.

Regional media monitoring: Set up monitoring for regional publications, Track regional social media mentions, Monitor regional news cycles and trends, and Measure regional share of voice.

Coordinating national and regional PR: Align messaging across markets, Sequence national and regional announcements, Avoid conflicting messages, and Create regional amplification of national news.',
    '[{"task": "Adapt core press materials for 3 regional markets", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Build regional journalist relationship plans", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Create region-specific story angles and talking points", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Set up regional media monitoring coverage", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "India PR Distribution Network", "url": "https://www.indiaprwire.com/", "type": "service"}, {"title": "Regional News Aggregators", "url": "https://www.dailyhunt.in/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "ShareChat Regional Social", "url": "https://sharechat.com/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Koo Indian Microblogging", "url": "https://www.kooapp.com/", "type": "platform"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'Regional Influencer Partnerships', 'Partner with regional influencers for amplified reach.',
    'Leveraging regional digital influencers.', 3, 40,
    'Regional influencers often have more engaged audiences than national English influencers. Partnering with regional creators extends brand reach into markets national strategies miss.

Regional influencer landscape: YouTube is massive in regional languages, Regional Instagram and Facebook creators, Moj and Josh for short video content, ShareChat for regional social engagement, and WhatsApp channels and groups.

Identifying regional influencers: Use platform native search in regional languages, Work with regional agencies who know local creators, Analyze engagement rates, not just followers, Verify authentic audiences versus purchased followers, and Assess brand alignment and content quality.

Regional influencer categories: Business and entrepreneurship influencers, Industry-specific experts, Lifestyle and aspirational creators, News and commentary creators, and Local celebrity and public figures.

Partnership models: Sponsored content creation, Product reviews and demonstrations, Event participation and coverage, Long-term ambassador relationships, and Co-creation of regional content.

Regional influencer negotiation: Rates vary significantly by region and language, Nano and micro influencers often deliver better engagement, Negotiate exclusivity carefully, Ensure clear deliverable specifications, and Build relationships for ongoing partnerships.

Content localization with influencers: Brief influencers on brand guidelines while allowing local adaptation, Review content for cultural appropriateness, Ensure proper disclosures for sponsored content, and Leverage influencer local knowledge.

Measuring regional influencer impact: Track regional traffic and engagement spikes, Monitor regional brand mention increases, Measure regional lead generation, Survey regional customers on discovery channels, and Calculate regional CAC from influencer channels.',
    '[{"task": "Research and shortlist 30 regional influencers across key markets", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Develop regional influencer partnership framework and rate guidelines", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Execute 3 regional influencer partnerships as pilots", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Create measurement framework for regional influencer ROI", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Moj Short Video Platform", "url": "https://mojapp.in/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Josh Short Videos", "url": "https://share.myjosh.in/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Winkl Influencer Platform", "url": "https://winkl.co/", "type": "platform"}, {"title": "Plixxo Influencer Marketing", "url": "https://www.plixxo.com/", "type": "platform"}]');

    -- MODULE 12: Brand Measurement
    INSERT INTO modules (product_id, title, description, order_index, duration_days)
    VALUES (v_product_id, 'Brand Measurement', 'Measure and optimize brand and PR performance.', 12, 4)
    RETURNING id INTO v_module_id;

    INSERT INTO lessons (module_id, title, description, content, order_index, duration_minutes, brief_content, action_items, resources) VALUES
    (v_module_id, 'Brand Health Metrics', 'Track key metrics that indicate brand health and growth.',
    'Measuring what matters for brand building.', 1, 45,
    'Brand building is a long-term investment—measuring its impact requires tracking the right metrics over time. Without measurement, you cannot optimize or prove ROI.

Brand awareness metrics: Unaided awareness (brand recalled without prompts), Aided awareness (brand recognized when mentioned), Share of voice (your mentions versus competitors), Search volume trends (brand name searches), and Direct traffic (people coming directly to your site).

Brand perception metrics: Brand attributes association (what qualities people associate), Net Promoter Score (likelihood to recommend), Brand favorability (positive versus negative sentiment), and Trust and credibility measures.

PR-specific metrics: Media coverage volume and quality, Share of voice in media, Message pull-through (key messages appearing in coverage), Spokesperson quote inclusion, Tier 1 media placement rate, and Coverage sentiment analysis.

Social media metrics: Follower growth and engagement rates, Share of voice on social platforms, Sentiment in social mentions, Influencer engagement and amplification, and Virality and share rates.

Business impact metrics: Brand-driven website traffic, Branded search to conversion rates, Customer acquisition cost by channel, Customer lifetime value by source, and Referral and word-of-mouth rates.

Setting up measurement: Establish baseline metrics before campaigns, Define target metrics and timeframes, Use consistent measurement methodology, Track trends over time, not just snapshots, and Benchmark against competitors where possible.

Measurement frequency: Real-time: social mentions, sentiment. Weekly: coverage volume, engagement. Monthly: share of voice, traffic trends. Quarterly: brand tracking surveys. Annually: comprehensive brand health assessment.',
    '[{"task": "Define your core brand health metrics and measurement approach", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Establish baseline measurements for key metrics", "priority": "high"}, {"task": "Set up dashboards for ongoing brand metric tracking", "priority": "medium"}, {"task": "Create competitive benchmarking for share of voice", "priority": "medium"}]',
    '[{"title": "Google Analytics for Brand Traffic", "url": "https://analytics.google.com/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "Brandwatch Social Listening", "url": "https://www.brandwatch.com/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "SimilarWeb Competitive Analysis", "url": "https://www.similarweb.com/", "type": "tool"}, {"title": "YouGov Brand Index", "url": "https://business.yougov.com/product/brandindex", "type": "research"}]'),

    (v_module_id, 'PR ROI Measurement', 'Calculate and demonstrate PR return on investment.',
    'Proving PR value to stakeholders.', 2, 40,
    'Demonstrating PR ROI is essential for securing continued investment. While brand building has long-term effects that are hard to attribute directly, rigorous measurement approaches provide evidence of value.

PR ROI framework components: Investment (agency fees, tools, team time, distribution costs), Outputs (coverage volume, placements, mentions), Outtakes (message delivery, audience reached, engagement), Outcomes (awareness, perception, behavior change), and Business impact (leads, sales, customer value).

Coverage valuation approaches: AVE (Advertising Value Equivalents)—widely used but criticized, Media impressions and reach calculations, Share of voice and competitive comparison, Quality-weighted coverage scoring, and Business outcome attribution.

Moving beyond AVE: AVE treats all coverage as equivalent to ad space, Better approaches track actual impact, Focus on quality metrics alongside quantity, and Link coverage to business outcomes.

Attribution models for PR: Direct attribution (tracking codes, unique URLs), Survey-based attribution (how did you hear about us?), Time-series analysis (correlating coverage with outcomes), Marketing mix modeling (statistical attribution), and Controlled experiments (where feasible).

Building a PR measurement dashboard: Coverage volume and quality trends, Share of voice and competitive position, Key message penetration, Social amplification of coverage, Website traffic from PR activities, and Lead and conversion attribution.

